text: Kitchen is closed! So no food, it stunk like ass and the bartenders had horrible attitudes! I would suggest they just close the place down!! TWO THUMBS DOWN!!

This place was pretty good.  The mixologist, Julia, was very knowledgeable and had a GREAT positive attitude.  She was very friendly and genuine, and talked to me and other patrons at the bar as if she's known us for years.  There were mostly locals hanging out there, and the vibe was pretty laid back and relaxing.  A bottle of IPA cost only $3.50.  I definitely plan on visiting there again soon!  

The only caution, is not to go hungry.  It says "Restaurant", but they do not have food.  That's the only negative thing I have to say about it.  Otherwise, I would highly recommend!

Stopped in for a quick pop and to see a friend who was there waiting for us.  Beers came in big glasses, and were comped over to us because we were playing video poker on the bar machines.  How cool is that?  Two free beers to lose $25 in the machines while drinking, but we had a good time talking and getting caught up in a nice, air-conditioned place with great service.

I come here quite often and haven't had a single bad experience. The drinks are delicious, calm atmosphere and Ali is the best. As soon as i walk in my drink is ready. It's hard to find a good place in town where you can just relax and take a breather.
